<% content_for(:title) { "Refund Policy - X-ROR" } %>
<% content_for(:seo_description) { "X-ROR Refund Policy. Learn about our refund eligibility, process, and timeline for paid subscriptions." } %>
<%= render "shared/navbar" %>
<main class="flex-1 pb-16">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pt-16 sm:px-6">
    <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Last updated: March 12, 2026</p>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight">Refund Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
      We want you to be satisfied with X-ROR. This Refund Policy explains when and how you can
      request a refund for paid subscriptions purchased through <strong>x-ror.fun</strong>.
    </p>

    <!-- 1. Refund Eligibility -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">1. Refund Eligibility</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      We offer a <strong>14-day money-back guarantee</strong> on your first paid subscription
      (Basic or Pro plan). If you are not satisfied with the Service within the first 14 days of
      your initial purchase, you may request a full refund &mdash; no questions asked.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">To be eligible for a refund:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li>Your request must be made within 14 days of your first paid subscription purchase.</li>
      <li>The refund applies only to your first subscription period (not renewals).</li>
      <li>One refund per user/account.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- 2. Non-Refundable Items -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">2. Non-Refundable Items</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">The following are not eligible for refunds:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li><strong>Renewal charges:</strong> monthly or annual renewal payments after your first billing period.</li>
      <li><strong>Partial months:</strong> we do not provide prorated refunds for unused portions of a billing period after the 14-day window.</li>
      <li><strong>Account termination for violations:</strong> if your account was terminated for violating our <%= link_to "Terms of Service", terms_path %>, no refund will be issued.</li>
      <li><strong>Previously refunded accounts:</strong> if you already received a refund and re-subscribed.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- 3. How to Request a Refund -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">3. How to Request a Refund</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">To request a refund:</p>
    <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li>Send an email to <a href="mailto:[SUPPORT_EMAIL]" class="underline hover:text-foreground">[SUPPORT_EMAIL]</a> with the subject line "Refund Request."</li>
      <li>Include your account email address and the reason for your request (optional but helpful).</li>
      <li>We will review your request and respond within <strong>5 business days</strong>.</li>
      <li>If approved, the refund will be processed to your original payment method via LiqPay within <strong>5&ndash;10 business days</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- 4. What Happens After a Refund -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">4. What Happens After a Refund</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">Once a refund is processed:</p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li>Your paid subscription will be cancelled immediately.</li>
      <li>Your account will be downgraded to the Free plan.</li>
      <li>You will lose access to paid features (batch downloads, stories, analyzer, influencer search, hashtag generator, API access).</li>
      <li>Your account and any saved data (bookmarks, history) will remain intact on the Free plan.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- 5. Billing Errors and Exceptions -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">5. Billing Errors and Exceptions</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      We will always make it right in the following situations, regardless of the 14-day window:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li><strong>Duplicate charges:</strong> if you were charged more than once for the same billing period, we will refund the duplicate(s).</li>
      <li><strong>Billing errors:</strong> if you were charged an incorrect amount, we will refund the difference or the full charge as appropriate.</li>
      <li><strong>Charges after cancellation:</strong> if you were charged after successfully cancelling your subscription, we will issue a full refund for that charge.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Contact us at <a href="mailto:[SUPPORT_EMAIL]" class="underline hover:text-foreground">[SUPPORT_EMAIL]</a>
      with details and we will resolve the issue promptly.
    </p>

    <!-- 6. Chargebacks -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">6. Chargebacks</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      We encourage you to contact us before initiating a chargeback (dispute) with your bank or
      payment provider. We are committed to resolving billing issues quickly and fairly.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      Filing a chargeback without contacting us first may result in your account being suspended
      until the dispute is resolved. Fraudulent chargebacks may lead to permanent account termination.
    </p>

    <!-- 7. EU Consumer Rights -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">7. EU Consumer Rights</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      If you are a consumer in the European Union, you may have a statutory right of withdrawal
      within 14 days of purchase under the Consumer Rights Directive. By using the Service during
      this period, you acknowledge that you have requested immediate access and that the right of
      withdrawal may be reduced accordingly. This policy does not limit any rights you have under
      applicable EU consumer protection laws.
    </p>
    <!-- LEGAL FLAG -->
    <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-yellow-500/30 bg-yellow-500/5 p-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
        <strong>&#9888; Legal review recommended:</strong> EU consumer withdrawal rights for digital
        services have specific requirements. Consult a lawyer to ensure your refund policy fully
        complies with the EU Consumer Rights Directive (2011/83/EU).
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 8. Contact -->
    <h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-bold">8. Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="mt-2 text-muted-foreground">
      For refund requests or billing questions, contact us at:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-muted-foreground">
      <li>Email: <a href="mailto:[SUPPORT_EMAIL]" class="underline hover:text-foreground">[SUPPORT_EMAIL]</a></li>
      <li>Website: <a href="https://x-ror.fun" class="underline hover:text-foreground">x-ror.fun</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</main>
